Type: Package
Package: Rootopia
Title: Depth-Resolved Root Analysis and Trait Extraction from Minirhizotrons and Flatbed Scanner
Version: 1.1.0
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Johannes",
             family = "Cunow",
             role = c("aut", "cre"),
             email = "johannes.cunow@gmail.com",
             comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0006-4830-1162")))
Maintainer: Johannes Cunow <johannes.cunow@gmail.com>
Description: Rootopia enables depth-resolved analysis of minirhizotron images and trait extraction from flatbed root scans. 
    Designed for studying root dynamics and morphology, it provides tools for root density, skeletonization, 
    depth profiling, and trait quantification. Track roots in depth. Extract traits in detail. 
    Rotational biases of minirhizotron tubes can also be assessed. 
    Minirhizotron scans will need to be segmented beforehand (e.g., 'RootDetector', 'RootPainter').
